        "rich_text_8DL9Df": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1st Para",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>When it comes to styling a look, most people focus just on their outfit, but the real beauty is in the details, such as the hairstyle and the accessories. Details can entirely transform an outfit; even if you have simply thrown on a pair of jeans and top, the hairstyle and the jewelry can make you look and feel elegant. At Lucira Jewelry, we believe that jewelry is not just an accessory, but a must needed style statement to elevate your look. Whether you like designer jewelry or minimalist jewelry, understanding how to style your outfit with different hairstyles and different jewelry pieces, you can effortlessly put together a look that you feel more beautiful, confident and elegant in.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bUfHBT": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Why Your Hairstyle Matters When Choosing Jewellery",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Why Your Hairstyle Matters When Choosing Jewellery</h2><p>Your hairstyle frames your face and creates a polished look, while your jewelry frames your hairstyle. Together, they can make or break the impact of your look based on how cohesively they are styled. For example, voluminous hair can easily hide delicate, minimal jewelry pieces, while a sleek ponytail can enhance every detail of your pendant chain or v neck necklace. </p><p>Your jewelry should complement your hairstyle and outfit without overwhelming your overall look. This is the secret of most stylists around the world, and is the key to create a refined look. In this blog, we have created a concise yet comprehensive to-dos to style your jewelry based on your hairstyle. </p>",
            "custom_id": "hairstyle",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_Jc4E4r": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Understanding Jewellery Types and Their Impact",
          "settings": {
