        },
        "image_with_text_YeQnaE": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Statement_Jewelry.jpg",
            "text": "<p>Bold, eye catching statement earrings become a focal point of the look. When paired with an outfit, statement earrings draw attention and do not need to be paired with a necklace to create a balanced look. Similarly, heavy necklace sets can be paired with small huggies, <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/hoop-earrings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lab Grown Diamond Hoop Earrings\">hoops</a> or studs. </p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": false,
            "products": []
          }
        },
        "rich_text_6WCWXy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Jewelry Necklace Sets ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Jewelry Necklace Sets </h3><p>The necklace and earrings combination, crafted to go together, is perfect for grand occasions such as festivals and weddings. The coordinated look enhances the beauty, while creating a refined and sophisticated look. </p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_xii4nX": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Hairstyle and Jewellery Pairing: A Brief Guide",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Hairstyle and Jewellery Pairing: A Brief Guide</h2>",
            "custom_id": "pairing",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_XQxqmB": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Hairstyle_and_Jewellery_Pairing_A_Brief_Guide_V2.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_fN3RJE": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Updos (Buns, Chignons, Sleek Ponytails)</h3><p>With hair swept away from the face and neck, updos create a blank canvas for jewelry while giving a clean look. The open neckline allows for an intricate and delicate necklace. Statement earrings like a dangler looks best with this style! Create a stylish look with layered jewellery. </p><h3>Loose Waves and Curls</h3><p>Soft loose hairstyles naturally add volume to hair. Minimal necklaces, pendant chains, or medium-sized hoops don’t overpower the look without getting hidden in the hair’s texture and volume. </p><h3>Short Hair and Pixie Cuts</h3><p>With short hair and pixie cuts, jewellery can be highlighted properly and it makes for the perfect opportunity to try different types of jewellery designs and textures. For instance, geometric minimalist jewellery and short chain necklaces look great! The cropped length exposes the neck and collarbone naturally, giving the jewellery prime visibility. </p><h3>Braids and Half-Up Styles</h3><p>If you have straight, side-parted hair or have a half up, half down hairstyle, a <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/tennis-bracelets\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lab Grown Diamond Tennis Bracelet\">tennis bracelet</a> adds elegance while looking smooth and playful. If you have braided hair, you can design your look with trend jewels or jewellery necklace as it adds an element to your styling while also giving you room to accessorize your hair. </p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_rQKzCe": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Matching Jewellery Metal to Hair Colour",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Matching Jewellery Metal to Hair Colour</h2><p>Metal color can either enhance or dull your look, based on how you pair the jewellery with your hair color. Warmer hair shades such as golden blonde, caramel brown, or auburn tend to glow against yellow gold. To create a cohesive and balanced look, style your hair of cooler shades such as blonde, blue, jet black, or espresso brown with white gold or platinum. For unique colored hair - think vivid reds or pastel pink, it’s a great opportunity to accessorize with necklaces that are trending, while mixing the metals and textures. For example, if you have red or burgundy colored hair, harmonize the look with jewellery with a unique styling choice - mixed metal jewellery such as white gold necklace and rose gold colored earrings. </p>",
            "custom_id": "metal",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_ADDTPa": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Common Mistakes to Avoid While Choosing Your Jewelry Based On Hairstyles ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Common Mistakes to Avoid While Choosing Your Jewelry Based On Hairstyles </h2><p>Here are some quick big NO’s while styling your jewellery based on hairstyles:</p><ul><li>Do not pair statement jewellery with open, voluminous hair</li><li>Do not pair dangling earrings with open, curly hair to avoid the jewellery getting tangled with your hair</li><li>Do not mismatch cooler hair color tones with golden jewellery - it will create a mismatched look </li><li>Do not ignore hair accessories - pins, colorful rubber bands, etc. If they are ornate, balance them with minimal jewelry to pull off a refined look. </li></ul>",
            "custom_id": "mistakes",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_CNg3En": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Conclusion",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Conclusion</h2><p>Jewellery and hairstyles are both styling tools, and can transform the entire look when done correctly. From wearing mixed metal jewelry to matching jewelry based on hairstyle and neckline, jewellery styling is fun and ensures that every element is perfectly co-ordinated to create a refined look. The right kind of styling can bring beauty to every detail and make any ordinary outfit look remarkable, with just a few tweaks with Lucira Jewelry’s styling tips!</p>",
            "custom_id": "conclusion",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        }
      },
